Change History

Revision Date Notes
9.0.0 2023-11-14 Added Diagnostics9 service to indicate support for system command execution in ExecSysCommand.
8.0.0 2019-07-29 Added Diagnostics8 service to indicate support for an IPv6 host address in StartTraceroute.
7.0.0 2019-06-11 Added Diagnostics7 service, which includes the following new JNAP action:
  • action GetSystemStats
6.0.1 2018-08-02 Moved Reliability Phase II services (Diagnostics6) to diagnostics4.hsl.
6.0.0 2018-07-16
  1. Made GetSysinfoData not transaction-safe as it is blocking.
  2. Added Diagnostics6 service. The followings were added:
    • action RequestSysinfoData2
    • action GetSysinfoRequestStatus2
    • action GetSysinfoData4
    • action GetSupportedSysinfoSections
  3. Removed Diagnostics4 and Diagnostics5 along with the followings:
    • enum SectionName
    • action RequestSysinfoData
    • action GetSysinfoRequestStatus
    • action GetSysinfoData3
    • action UploadSysinfoData
5.0.0 2016-05-02 Added Diagnostics5 service, which includes the following new JNAP actions to get Sysinfo diagnostics data asynchronously:
  • action RequestSysinfoData
  • action GetSysinfoRequestStatus
  • action GetSysinfoData3
4.0.0 2016-02-12 Added Diagnostics4 service that supports configuration of diagnostic data collection and uploads (Reliability Phase II).

Added the following:
  • action GetDiagnosticsSettings
  • action SetDiagnosticsSettings
  • action GetSysinfoData2
  • action UploadSysinfoData

Actions

ExecSysCommand

http://linksys.com/jnap/diagnostics/ExecSysCommand
This action executes the system command for diagnostic. This call is synchronous and is blocking. Please don't use this if you're not sure about the risk.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
cmd string no The executed command
param string yes The extra parameters for the command

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
cmdresult string no The command execution result data

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/diagnostics/ExecSysCommandResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorExecSysCommadFailed The command process failed
ErrorExecSysCommadNotSupport The command doesn't support
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorDisallowedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/diagnostics/ExecSysCommand"

{
  "cmd": "example string",
  "param": "example string"
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK",
  "output": {
    "cmdresult": "example string"
  }
}

GetPingStatus

http://linksys.com/jnap/diagnostics/GetPingStatus
This action gets the status of the ping test.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

This action does not have any input parameters.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
isRunning bool no Whether the ping test is currently running.
pingLog string no The output of the pending or most recently completed ping test.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/diagnostics/GetPingStatusResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/diagnostics/GetPingStatus"

{
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK",
  "output": {
    "isRunning": true,
    "pingLog": "PING 192.168.10.1: 32 data bytes"
  }
}

SendSysinfoEmail

http://linksys.com/jnap/diagnostics/SendSysinfoEmail
This action sends an email message containing the sysinfo diagnostic data, as an attachment, to a list of email addresses.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
addressList string[] no List of email addresses to which the message will be sent.

Output Parameters

This action does not have any output parameters.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/diagnostics/SendSysinfoEmailResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorAlreadyRunning A failure occurred sending the email.
ErrorEmptyAddressList The input addressList is empty.
ErrorInvalidEmailAddress An email address specified in the addressList is invalid.
ErrorSendFailed A failure occurred sending the email.
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/diagnostics/SendSysinfoEmail"

{
  "addressList": [
    "example string"
  ]
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK"
}

StartPing

http://linksys.com/jnap/diagnostics/StartPing
This service provides access to diagnostic utilities. This action starts a ping test.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
host string no The IP or URL to ping. This must be a valid IPv4 address in dotted-quad notation, a valid IPv6 address in or a valid host name as defined in RFCs 952 and 1123.
packetSizeBytes int no The ping packet size in bytes. This value must be between 32 and 65500.
pingCount int yes The number of times to ping the host. If this value is not specified, the number of pings is unlimited and the test will continue until StopPing is called. If specified, this value must be greater than 0.

Output Parameters

This action does not have any output parameters.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/diagnostics/StartPingResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorInvalidHost The specified host is invalid.
ErrorInvalidPacketSizeBytes The specified packet size is invalid.
ErrorInvalidPingCount The specified ping count is invalid.
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorDisallowedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/diagnostics/StartPing"

{
  "host": "192.168.10.1",
  "packetSizeBytes": 32,
  "pingCount": 10
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK"
}
